  <h2>El Dorado's Industrial History and Its Housing</h2>
  <p>The oil industry built a lot of El Dorado. Many of the older neighborhoods near downtown were worker housing from the refinery era — modest homes, smaller lots, mostly built between 1910 and 1950. These properties need work, and the buyer pool for them is thin in a town of 13,000.</p>
  <p>El Dorado also has a significant rental property market. Landlords who bought during the low-price years are now aging out of active management and looking to liquidate. Tenant-occupied properties with deferred maintenance are something we buy — no eviction required before closing.</p>
